text: The Stolley Homestead Site is a historic house in Grand Island, Nebraska. It was built in 1858-1859 as a log cabin by William Stolley, an immigrant from Schleswig-Holstein, Germany. With The property was acquired by the state of Nebraska in 1927. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since March 16, 1972. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Hall County, Nebraska Category:Houses completed in 1857 Category:1857 establishments in Nebraska Territory
title: Stolley Homestead Site
